
From LM 59 - april 2012

Using Pathogen to activate vim extensions.
Two folders:
autoload -> Pathogen
bundle -> installed extensions

.vimrc is a soft link to .vim/vimrc


extensions:
pep8: recomended python code rules
pyflakes: python syntax validation
MiniBufferExplorer: tab manager
Command-T: quick file open -> <\> + t
NERD Tree: file navigation and open -> F9
TagList: keyword navigation -> F8
SuperTab: auto completion -> TAB; activate Django completion -> F10
PyDoc: python documentation
RopeVim: code navigation; goto definition -> F6; rename -> F7
TaskList: task list management (TODO, FIXME!) NOT INSTALLED...
SnipMate: snippets management
snipmate_for_django
Gundo: vim file change history
Pytest: call python unitary tests
fugitive: git control from vim
